 TSHAKHUMA, Limpopo - The Limpopo Health Department says it's concerned people coming to the province could increase the number of coronavirus cases. So far, it has only one confirmed case, but the department's biggest worry is the virus reaching rural areas. READ: Coronavirus: Limpopo takes precautionary measures The Tshakhuma Community Fruit Market is popular with locals, as well as people coming from afar. The traders are interacting with people daily. READ: More COVID-19 tests needed: Mkhize But with the coronavirus outbreak, is it safe? There is no social distancing or avoiding contact and hands are used in all exchanges. READ: COVID-19: How many people will die? The health department is desperate to ensure there are no more confirmed cases. It hopes the virus won't spread, and especially not to villages.